Text.Value: Fytz! Congratulations! That's amazing news.
Must've been hard for you not to have a go at him then and there. Gregor doesn't see the big deal, but he doesn't know Gortash like we do.
I never took you for the parental type.
Plenty of those going around. Gortash really broke hard in the wrong direction this last decade.
Meanwhile, if you're still in the business of intimidation, I might have something you can make use of in the shop.
Almost had you there. Hello, Fytz.
Well, we both know he deserved it. Incredible. You vanish for ten years, then come back and murder the biggest prick in the city. Legend.
Ha! Woman, I haven't seen that ugly mug of yours in ten years. But if you can stick around long enough to prove you mean it, you've got the job. You're my oldest friend, after all.
Can I be the godsmother?
For now. No one can resist the ol' Karlach charm for long.
You look a little different, but I'd know my old friend anywhere.

EditorData.NodeContext: Karlach is disguised as another person

Text.Value: Let me see your wares.
I would have if I could. But it's a long story.
Me either. I wasn't sure I was ready - that I'd ever be ready. But it just happened one day, and let me tell you, it all just made sense somehow.
See you soon, Karlach.
There is. I'd love to introduce you properly sometime. Maybe over a flagon of something dry?
Good you got out while you could.
Hope you found what you were looking for.
Don't I know it.
Myself included among them. I'm so glad you're back.
Gregor's my fella. We've been together eight years now. And - Karlach - we've a little one on the way.
Neverwinter?! Who told you I was in Neverwinter?!
Where the hells have you been, girl? Last I heard you'd run off to Neverwinter. And that was, what, ten years ago?
Hahaha! Oh my gods. You didn't. Did you?!

EditorData.NodeContext: First joking, then realizing she's serious.

Text.Value: Didn't you hear? I killed that motherfucker.
That's my fella. We've been together eight years now. And - Karlach - we've a little one on the way.
That's exactly what I said. He's going to be the death of this place, mark my words. Gregor thinks I'm biased.
What's got you in such a hurry?
Forget all that. How are you?
Gods, I'd love that. We have so much to catch up on.
I guess that's technically true.
Thank you, thank you. Even after all these years, it seemed to happen so fast. But I couldn't be happier.
I've believed every word out of that mouth of yours since I was ten years old.
Anyway, how can I help you?
I'm sorry, Fytz, but I've got to run. I'm in town on very urgent business.
Didn't you hear? I killed that motherfucker.
Met my fella Gregor that way. We've been together eight years now. And - Karlach - we've a little one on the way.
Not like that. But I've got some very dear friends.
You'd better stock up, woman.
I won't lie to you, girl - the years have been good.
You look a little different, but I'd know my old friend anywhere.

EditorData.NodeContext: Karlach is disguised as another person

Text.Value: Leave.
Karlach Cliffgate. That can't possibly be you, can it?
I left Gortash's gang not long after you. Started working for an arms merchant - still in the trade, as you can see.
Don't worry. I'm going to deal with him.
Anyone special in your life?
Come find me when you're done doing what you're doing. I'll be here - dawn to dusk on the daily.
Fytz. If you aren't a sight for sore eyes.
Don't worry. I'm going to deal with him.
Gortash said you didn't even give notice.
Sorry, I think you have the wrong person.
If anyone can handle him, it's you. Just don't get yourself locked up - not now that you're home.
He's a liar. Always has been, I now realise.
The prick's a liar.
It's just me.
Give 'em hell, Karlach.
Sorry - you've got the wrong person.
KARLACH! I knew it was you, you arsehole. You had me thinking I was seeing visions.
A long, shitty story. I'd love to sit down with a pint and tell 'em all to you, Fytz.
Do I? But you look just like her. Minus one horn.
Now that you're back in town, you must come to ours. All of you. We'll have a good supper, catch up. You can meet Gregor. And the little one, in a few months.
I'll give you all the gory details when we can talk in private.
Karlach Cliffgate. That can't possibly be you, can it?

EditorData.NodeContext: An old friend spotting someone she hasn't seen in 10 years.

Text.Value: Archduke Fox lording it over the hen house. What could go wrong?
It's been so long. Gortash said you fled north - didn't even give notice. I did wonder why you never wrote.
I saw red when I found out.
After I left Gortash's gang, I fell into merchantry, as you can see. Met a fella called Gregor. We've been together eight years now. And - Karlach - we've a little one on the way.
I knew it! Karlach, my gods!
Seeing as how no one's thrown you in jail yet, I suppose you got away with the crime, did you? If you're not a wanted criminal, I'd love to have you over.
Leave.
Would you believe me if I said I've got to save the city?
Fytz! Congratulations!
Fytz. If you aren't a sight for sore eyes.
I think you were the only thing that kept him a little honest. After you left, things got dark, fast. I got out while my soul was still intact.
Never mind for now. Bye, Fytz.
D'you see he's the Archduke now? What the fuck, right?
Finish your business in the city, then we'll arrange a proper catch-up, all right?
Funny. Well, your long lost twin was an old friend of mine. Haven't seen her in ten years, but... well, I guess she must still be off in Neverwinter, or wherever she vanished to.

Synopsis: Karlach reunites with her old friend Fytz in Baldur's gate.
